rman French <i>boschet</i> ‘copse, thicket’ (a diminutive of   Bois  ) + <i>ville</i> ‘settlement, town’."],"variants":[{"name":"Bois","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alcide, Antoine, Donat, Marcel, Ovide, Ovila, Raoul, Serge.","French: topographic name for someone living or working in a wood, from (Old) French <i>bois</i> ‘wood’ (from Late Latin <i>boscum</i> ‘bush, shrub, undergrowth’, of ancient Germanic origin), or a habitational name from (Le) Bois, the name of several places in various parts of France. This surname is also found in Haiti. Compare   Debois   and the most frequent French form   Dubois  . Compare also   Boie  ,   Boies  , and   Boyce  .","English: variant of   Boyce   and   Boyes  ."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Ralph Baskerville was born on 21 October 1410, in Eardisley, Herefordshire, England, his father, Sir John Baskerville, was 24 and his mother, Joan Brydges, was 21. He married Anne Blackett in 1438, in Eardisley, Herefordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1446, in Stow on the Wold, Gloucestershire, England, at the age of 36."},"et":{"21 October 1410–1446":"21. oktoober 1410–1446","1408–1455":"1408–1455","1410–1446":"1410–1446","1428–1500":"1428–1500","1412–1442":"1412–1442","1439–1488":"1439–1488","1387–1415":"1387–1415","1389–143